text.text: Nicole is such a big help!! You can definitely tell that she loves these babies. She is also incredibly knowledgeable as far as the vetting. Excellent customer service along with a beautiful welcoming smile and kind eyes!! Nicole truly will treat you like a family member and strive to help these babies find forever homes. Thank you Nicole for making my experience here an unforgettable outstanding one. The love you have in your heart for these fur babies definitely shines bright. Thank you for the friendliest customer service I have ever received. If you’re in the market for a kitty, I definitely recommend Nicole to help you find the right fit.
They’re the best! I go here on Fridays during my lunch break for my end of the work week serotonin boost and they always deliver. 20/10 would recommend!

My wife and I LOVE this place!! We adopted 3 cats from Cattiesburg Cafe over the past year. And all of them are wonderful. I love that the cafe gives you an opportunity to really know the cats before you commit. Plus it’s just a great place to relax if you aren’t looking to adopt! 10/10 would recommend!

cafes.name: Cat Island Coffeehouse Gulfport
cafes.address: 360 Courthouse Rd C, Gulfport, MS 39507, USA

text.text: This is such a great coffee shop. It has a very warm and welcome environment. Everyone was very nice. Service was excellent!!! The coffee and food were delicious. There are books and books posters framed on the walls. I will definitely visit again.

The atmosphere is wonderful!!!  Very relaxing and have a delicious gourmet coffee. I've been all over the world and this place impressed me.  The food was fresh and flavorful. They even asked if I'm a sweet or non sweet coffee drinker which majority of places never do.  If you are looking for good food,coffee, and atmosphere.  You have to give this place a try.

Everything you want in a cozy coffee house. The staff are all warm and welcoming. The Mississippi Mocha is perfect, as is the amazing buttery croissant.  I chose sausage, egg, and chedar. It was flaky gooey perfection.  The book collection is refreshingly diverse and has a little something for everyone, and yes, you are welcome to read through one while you enjoy your food and beverages.

cafes.name: Cat Island Coffeehouse
cafes.address: 300 E Scenic Dr, Pass Christian, MS 39571, USA

text.text: Really cool coffee shop/book store. If you're looking for a cozy place to grab some coffee and read a book, then look no further. This place is somewhat quiet and very cozy. I could hang out here all day drinking coffee while reading a book.

There are a few great coffee shops along the Gulf Coast of Mississippi and Cat Island Coffee Shop ranks near the top. The coffee and Lattes are great but the views of the MS sound are what sets it apart. The seating is limited but we have always had a place to sit and an excellent experience. It's a great place to stop off when driving the beach on a pretty day.

A very special little Coffee and Book haven situated across the Beach Hwy from the Gulf and the Pass Christian Harbor.  It is located right on the corner.
This place is so warm and comfortable. While you enjoy their wonderful coffee brews accompanied  by selections of b'fast sandwiches or cobbler or muffins, etc. I was in town visiting a great couple that live just down the elevated road. They walk down to the coffeehouse just about every day. That is informative about the coffee consistency, because my buddy, Artie is very frugal...

I had such an amazing time at Fat Cat this Valentine’s Day! Even though it was super busy, the owner, Pepper,  took time to speak to us and even captured a picture of us painting! She was so was so welcoming and helped make my Valentine’s Day painting date a memory I will always cherish.

We did a pottery class here and it was a great experience! Andrea was an amazing teacher. However during the last part of the class, the owner of the shop came in and was incredibly controlling and condescending. It really threw off the energy of the group and I don’t think we’ll be going back.

My wife & I did the canvas painting & it was awesome! You have a template so that you don’t have to be an expert w/ perspective or proportionality - you just paint!

And it’s not paint by number: you are free to mix paints to achieve what you want. I was so delighted with the results! A thoroughly enjoyable evening.

cafes.name: Crazy Cat Eat Up
cafes.address: 1491 Canton Mart Rd, Jackson, MS 39211, USA

text.text: What an amazing place to eat and hang out with your friends. The food is DIVINE and the atmosphere is great!! The wait staff are absolutely wonderful. Very friendly and helpful. The food tho...we have some pretty amazing places to satisfy our tummies in JXN and the surrounding areas. This place is easily in the top 3. Thinking I will even put it at the very top of my own personal list. It will not disappoint, you MUST give them a try!! Get the Crazy Good Veggie Sammie 😉

This was such a cute place to have brunch. We got there at almost closing and our waitress sat us down without complaining she was so nice and very helpful with recommendations.  We didn't feel rushed we kept an eye on the time ourselves. It truly was a wonderful experience from food to service!!
Fun place for unique treats. Our girls' lunch was a big hit. But show up early or be prepared to wait- it's a popular spot. But definitely worth the wait.
